<span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have been working closely with the households that will be impacted by the changes. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In the lead up to the implementation </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">we </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">identified, based on the data held at the time, that there were approximately 6,600 Home Group general needs households set to be af</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fected by the under-occupancy penalty – approximately 4,400 by 14% and 2,200 by 25%.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> We have identified affected customers through the number of bedrooms detailed in their tenancy agreement and through working closely with the local authority responsible </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">for their housing benefit. Liaising with local authority partners has been difficult and required significant extra resource to confirm benefit details – particularly for an organisation the size of Home Group as we </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">manage properties</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">over 200</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> local auth</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ority areas.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We’ve promoted widely the possibility of mutual exchange and Ho</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">me Swapper services, including mutual e</span><span